## Frontend Standard Rulebook 🎯🧩

### Golden Path (SRP-first) 🧠➡️🧩
- One component = one responsibility. Split early, not late.
- One hook = one concern. No “do-everything” hooks.
- One file = one main idea. Move helpers to `utils/` or `hooks/`.

### Naming (easy to remember) 🏷️✨
- Use clear names: `UserProfileCard`, `useThemePreference`, `formatReadableDate`.
- No short names unless domain-standard (`id`, `url`).
- Avoid “magic” names like `data`, `thing`, `stuff`.

### Constants (centralize policies) 🧰📍
- All timeouts, retries, sizes, limits, and durations live in `app/constants/policy.ts`.
- Never hardcode policy values in components or hooks.

### Configs (centralize config)
- All the config should be added to directory `app/config/*`.

### Type Safety & Props 🔒🧪
- Prefer explicit types for public component props.
- Keep props minimal; pass only what the component needs.
- Avoid `any`. If unavoidable, add a TODO only when explicitly asked.

### UI Structure (predictable layout) 🧭🧱
- Keep layout-only logic in `app/components/layout/`.
- Presentation components should be side-effect free.
- No data fetching inside layout components.

### State & Effects ⚙️🌊
- Keep side effects in `useEffect` with clear dependencies.
- Use derived state instead of duplicating data.
- If state is shared across pages, lift to a dedicated provider.

### CSS & Visual Consistency 🎨🧵
- Prefer CSS variables for colors, spacing, and typography.
- Keep class lists short; extract repeated styles to shared classes.

### Error Handling & UX 🛡️🧑‍🚀
- Always render a stable fallback UI for async or error states.
- Log errors once with context, not on every render.

### Testing & Accessibility ✅♿
- Add `aria-*` where intent isn’t obvious.
- Ensure keyboard focus styles are visible.
- A unit test should be localise to same directory where code is written.

### Visual Flow Map (SRP) 🗺️
```
Request -> Page -> Layout -> Feature Component -> UI Atoms
              |        |              |
              |        |              +-> Local state only
              |        +-> No data fetch
              +-> Data fetch (if needed)
```